<h2 id="my-favorite-terminal-application">My favorite terminal application</h2>

<p><img src="/images/posts/linux/terminator.png" alt="Terminator icon" /></p>

<p><a href="https://launchpad.net/terminator/">Terminator</a> allows you to open multiple terminals in one window, which can boost your productivity by operating two or more shells side by side or in grids.</p>

<p>It can be installed to Ubuntu by running the following code:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get <span class="nb">install </span>terminator
</code></pre></div></div>

